      "title": "See also"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "There are several common variants of the array variance calculation.\nAssuming the input "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "a"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is a one-dimensional NumPy array and "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/ops/mean",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "mean",
              "text": "mean"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is\neither provided as an argument or computed as "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "a.mean()"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ", NumPy\ncomputes the variance of an array as:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "language": null,
          "text": "N = len(a)\nd2 = abs(a - mean)**2  # abs is for complex `a`\nvar = d2.sum() / (N - ddof)  # note use of `ddof`",
          "type": "literal_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Different values of the argument "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "ddof"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " are useful in different\ncontexts. NumPy's default "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "ddof=0"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " corresponds with the expression:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "formulas": [
            "\\frac{\\sum_i{|a_i - \\bar{a}|^2 }}{N}"
          ],
          "type": "math_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "which is sometimes called the \"population variance\" in the field of\nstatistics because it applies the definition of variance to "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "a"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " as if "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "a"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "\nwere a complete population of possible observations."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Many other libraries define the variance of an array differently, e.g.:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "formulas": [
            "\\frac{\\sum_i{|a_i - \\bar{a}|^2}}{N - 1}"
          ],
          "type": "math_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "In statistics, the resulting quantity is sometimes called the \"sample\nvariance\" because if "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "a"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is a random sample from a larger population,\nthis calculation provides an unbiased estimate of the variance of the\npopulation.  The use of "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "N-1"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " in the denominator is often called\n\"Bessel's correction\" because it corrects for bias (toward lower values)\nin the variance estimate introduced when the sample mean of "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "a"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is used\nin place of the true mean of the population. For this quantity, use\n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "ddof=1"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Note that for complex numbers, the absolute value is taken before\nsquaring, so that the result is always real and nonnegative."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "For floating-point input, the variance is computed using the same\nprecision the input has.  Depending on the input data, this can cause\nthe results to be inaccurate, especially for "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "float32"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " (see example\nbelow).  Specifying a higher-accuracy accumulator using the "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "dtype"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "\nkeyword can alleviate this issue."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "import whest as we"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "a = we.array([[1, 2], [3, 4]])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.var(a)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "1.25"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.var(a, axis=0)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([1.,  1.])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.var(a, axis=1)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([0.25,  0.25])"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "In single precision, var() can be inaccurate:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "a = we.zeros((2, 512*512), dtype=we.float32)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "a[0, :] = 1.0"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "a[1, :] = 0.1"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.var(a)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "we.float32(0.20250003)"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Computing the variance in float64 is more accurate:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.var(a, dtype=we.float64)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "0.20249999932944759 # may vary"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "((1-0.55)**2 + (0.1-0.55)**2)/2"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "0.2025"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Specifying a where argument:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "a = we.array([[14, 8, 11, 10], [7, 9, 10, 11], [10, 15, 5, 10]])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.var(a)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "6.833333333333333 # may vary"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.var(a, where=[[True], [True], [False]])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "4.0"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Using the mean keyword to save computation time:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "import whest as we"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "from timeit import timeit"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": ""
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "a = we.array([[14, 8, 11, 10], [7, 9, 10, 11], [10, 15, 5, 10]])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "mean = we.mean(a, axis=1, keepdims=True)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": ""
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "g = globals()"
